How is it possible not to be astounded by the Lemuro-Sumerian formula 90 + 81 + 72 + 63 +54 = 360? ...
.... And what then to make of the Atlantean rejoinder 91 + 82 + 73 + 64 + 55 = 365, which still further mocks the presumed astro-mechanical contingency of the calendrical year?
Then go the other way, and ask yourself about the length of the sacred year. Or about the supposed incongruity of Sumerian sexagesimal and decimal metrics.
